Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.43,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(800,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.70,0:00:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.27,0:00:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.87,0:01:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.68,0:01:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rishid... The darkness of death has come for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.98,0:01:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a {\i1}friend{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.23,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your other half.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.44,0:01:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}piece{\i0} of Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.28,0:01:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.66,0:01:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you stick around a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.41,0:01:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to kill Rishid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.08,0:01:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's {\i1}your{\i0} turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.13,0:01:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My arm...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.50,0:01:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.26,0:02:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who were chosen by the Millennium Items...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.22,0:02:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...must settle things in a {\i1}Dark Game{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.35,0:02:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My {\i1}pleasure{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.89,0:02:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dark Malik VS Dark Bakura"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.75,0:02:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.05,0:02:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was really worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You alright now, Mai?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi, you're a much better Duelist than you used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.10,0:02:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm glad I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Goodbye...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.40,0:02:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:02:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}MAI!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.07,0:03:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me, Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.35,0:03:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ra has three Special Abilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Hieratic Text is a text written by the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So why am {\b0}I{\b1} able to read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.61,0:03:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But for now, I must focus on coming up with a strategy to beat Ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Dark Duel...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A game of death where the loser dies!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, {\i1}you'll{\i0} be the one dieing, Bakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.79,0:03:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.09,0:03:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...before the darkness fills your {\i1}mouth{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.38,0:04:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I remember correctly,\N Bakura fell against Yugi's Osiris.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.11,0:04:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then during the third Duel,\N when I crushed that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, he was lying\N in {\b0}bed{\b1} during those events.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Therefore, Bakura hasn't even seen the God Card I hold,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.37,0:04:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}nor does he know what the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can {\i1}see{\i0} him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The soul of my dominate half is beside you, telling you all my secrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw that, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your alter ego is my partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means I know your {\i1}entire deck{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it was {\b0}weak{\b1}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When our personalities changed,\N I added {\b0}many{\b1} new cards of my {\b0}own{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're a user of the God Cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.94,0:05:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.19,0:05:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you know that much,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you've got no way of {\i1}countering{\i0} my god!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.87,0:05:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enjoy coming up with a useless strategy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let us begin this Duel, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.46,0:05:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before we start, your other half has something to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.59,0:05:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you the evil self that {\b0}I{\b1} created?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.68,0:05:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness that\N built a nest in your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatred...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And out of that nest hatched {\i1}me{\i0}, the embodiment of your darkest desires!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Rishid sealed you away...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even sealed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still helped you by taking away the guilt deep within your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A "thank you" would be nice, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I learned some new information I found to be very interesting through the power of the Millennium Rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I learned everything through the girl I brainwashed, Anzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My sister told me\N the {\b0}truth{\b1} of the Ishtars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's start with {\b0}your{\b1} bloodbath,\N my dear father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stop it...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth being that is was {\b0}you{\b1} who killed my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.56,0:06:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey! You and I\N are two minds in one body!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't act like {\i1}you{\i0} aren't responsible, just because {\i1}I{\i0} had the upper hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're {\i1}just{\i0} as guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's true that the idea came from my own heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.29,0:06:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father... What have I done...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel so {\i1}bad{\i0} for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Five years ago,\N at that very same moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The one who caused this destiny was the soul of the great Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Pharaoh will revive soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go search for the Pharaoh, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The man who appeared\N before me that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Somehow I thought {\b0}he{\b1} was the resurrection of the Pharaoh's soul and that {\b0}he{\b1} killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But that wasn't the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what are you trying to say, my precious dominant half?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Both you and I are both guilty for my father's death, and we will be destroyed together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keh! How amusing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.25,0:07:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That turban-wearing man Malik just spoke of...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It had to have been Shadi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But five years ago he was already...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.85,0:07:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll support you with a strategy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't order me around!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you have to do is come through on our agreement!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.19,0:07:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you beat him, I'll give you the Millennium Rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.13,0:07:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not all. I want you to tell me the secret of the carvings on your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.19,0:07:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought putting all seven Millennium Items in the stone slate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:08:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would give me the Power of Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless I decode the hieroglyphs carved on your back,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the door can't be opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.45,0:08:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All right... I promise to tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.62,0:08:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you win, you don't care if your body is burned to ashes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.06,0:08:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't care!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.13,0:08:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.80,0:08:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can kill him without {\i1}worrying{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.52,0:08:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Done with your little discussion?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.77,0:08:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you two talked about,\N you're wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys like you... I kill instantly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.11,0:08:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start the Dark Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.42,0:08:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this Dark Duel, the loser's body and soul will be consumed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.67,0:08:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the ultimate death game!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.69,0:08:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Body and soul {\i1}consumed{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get it soon {\i1}enough{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.46,0:08:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DUEL!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.40,0:09:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! I draw a card first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.84,0:09:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set a powerful trap in the first round!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.37,0:09:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know {\b0}all about{\b1} your Occult Deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.58,0:09:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go! I'll set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I Summon\N Goblin Zombie in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.82,0:09:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.29,0:09:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Drillago!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the enemy Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, Fearful Earthbound, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.44,0:09:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.28,0:09:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used a Monster with low Attack Points as a decoy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.35,0:09:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to activate the trap card,\N Fearful Earthbound!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.06,0:09:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fearful Earthbound...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:10:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time the enemy player\N attacks one of your Monsters, they'll take 500 points of damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.37,0:10:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop\N my Monster from attacking!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and beat\N my weakling Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.01,0:10:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more Monsters you send to the Graveyard, the stronger my Occult Deck gets!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.48,0:10:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only {\i1}then{\i0} does its {\i1}true{\i0} power shine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment, the Effect of my Permanent Trap Card is activated!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.42,0:10:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthbound! Chew the player up!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to spoil your plans!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate! Remove Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.07,0:10:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Remove Trap's Effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.67,0:10:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthbound is negated!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you had an anti-trap card...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Bakura... Now it's {\i1}your{\i0} turn to take a look at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:10:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it was {\i1}you{\i0} that was bitten!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.86,0:11:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what the {\i1}hell{\i0} is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a Dark Duel\N between you and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.53,0:11:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.50,0:11:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost Life Points because of my attack just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this Dark Game,\N whenever you lose points...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness eats\N the player's body away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.36,0:11:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So hidden in that darkness is a beast that devours souls...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.85,0:11:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I {\i1}see{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This game is going to be rather {\i1}fun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.53,0:11:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you lose {\i1}all{\i0} your Life Points, you will be eaten by the void, both body and soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.46,0:11:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my Death Game!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.73,0:11:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So when your Life hits zero, you become a part of the darkness, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.91,0:11:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who will annihilate who?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.52,0:12:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.17,0:12:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is inside of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.18,0:12:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? I have a bad feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.95,0:12:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's wrong in the Other Me's Soul Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.16,0:12:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's been a long time since I walked into my other self's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.36,0:12:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's changed.\N It's still a vastly complicated maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.17,0:13:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you sleepwalk into my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You scared me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.85,0:13:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt something strange\N from your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.55,0:13:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I've been feeling it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.89,0:13:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I came here, I didn't understand what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I think I've got something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.63,0:13:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.60,0:13:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.07,0:13:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this room is like a map of your soul that isn't sure which path to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.18,0:13:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... one day I'll help get your memory back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.78,0:13:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe this is my task.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who will be devoured by the darkness first and be destroyed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.69,0:13:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How amusing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.02,0:13:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.73,0:13:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Choose your cards carefully, Bakura...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:14:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know your Occult Deck inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.47,0:14:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he knows my Occult Combo so well,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't use the Ouija Board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.08,0:14:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll just have to try a new strategy that Malik has has never {\b0}seen{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.48,0:14:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Bring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra sleeps in my deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.88,0:14:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It will kill you no matter {\b0}what{\b1} you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.99,0:14:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! What's {\i1}wrong{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.09,0:14:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.06,0:14:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik has one Monster on his field...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.30,0:14:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Suppose he's already got the God Card in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he gets three sacrifices on the field, he'll be able to Summon God...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.54,0:14:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't be afraid of God, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.69,0:14:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better stay quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.14,0:14:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is a way to make Ra powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.42,0:14:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey! Are you two having your "strategy planning time" again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me tell you something. It's futile!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:14:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.89,0:14:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} your plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.56,0:15:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rejoice{\i0}, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll blast your body apart\N using your own advice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.53,0:15:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't care! Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.18,0:15:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn dominate half...\N What'd he tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set two reverse cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.54,0:15:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I Summon one Wall Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just what is this guy planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.62,0:15:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But no matter {\b0}what{\b1} he does,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.49,0:15:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's futile before my God Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But, the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra is not in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I'll {\b0}make{\b1} God come to me using this Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.30,0:15:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate!\N Treasure from Heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hand reinforcement Magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct! We both draw from our decks until we hold six cards in our hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:16:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the look on your face, you still haven't drawn the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra into your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me give you a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.69,0:16:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open! Dying Altogether!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.46,0:16:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.60,0:16:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dying Altogether is a Trap Card that forces us to send our entire hand to the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then lets us draw five more cards in their place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.21,0:16:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the player who activates this Trap
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.61,0:16:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,loses 100 Life Points\N for every card he discards
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which results in only me\N losing Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.48,0:16:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why would he go so far just so I can draw the God Card...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the holdup?!\N Just hurry up and {\i1}draw{\i0} already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.85,0:16:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Still{\i0} nothing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.46,0:16:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the {\i1}hell{\i0}? You {\i1}still{\i0} haven't drawn it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}suck{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.47,0:16:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card\N and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.64,0:16:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember when someone came to this room before?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.11,0:16:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shadi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the power of the Millennium Key to see if somewhere in this maze
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lied the "true room of my soul" and the door that leads to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.97,0:17:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, he never was able to find that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.67,0:17:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... The truth is, I don't even know where the door is myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finding that door in a complicated\Nmaze like this is extremely difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Shadi appeared again on the Battle Ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.04,0:17:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All the requirements needed to open the door
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.25,0:17:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to the Pharaoh's memories are gathered aboard this Battle Ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door of the Pharaoh's memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:17:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's just somewhere in this maze...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's really your "true room"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.64,0:17:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't afford to lose these Duels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.37,0:18:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner, I'll win for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.21,0:18:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll gather all the requirements
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.31,0:18:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And open my door myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.55,0:18:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.72,0:18:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fight for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.55,0:18:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.22,0:18:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}my{\i0} turn! Card draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got it! I've been {\b0}waiting{\b1} for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Gelnia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the\N Puppet Master, Controller of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.57,0:18:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I activate\N Puppet Master's Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the player sacrificing 1000 Life Points as a cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they can call back three Monsters from the grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Monsters Special Summoned by Puppet Master can't attack in the same turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that! Just calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.60,0:19:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna give you a nice little present.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.61,0:19:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this Magic Card, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, Dark Designator, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.11,0:19:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Designator is a card that lets you declare a Monster Card name,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.87,0:19:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if they have it, the opponent adds the card to their hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.05,0:19:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking the Ra card sleeping in your deck and placing it in your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.49,0:19:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does it feel to finally get Ra?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.19,0:19:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} what you're up to...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.63,0:19:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.31,0:19:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you fools went to such lengths to allow me to draw my God Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You left a huge hint lying around on your side of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.64,0:19:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lowered your Life Points greatly just to play three weakling Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you still have that one reverse card on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You plan to steal my Ra, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.99,0:19:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bit too late to notice {\i1}now{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:20:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open! Exchange, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.45,0:20:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the effect of Exchange,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both players choose one card from the other's hand and exchange it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Give me your Ra card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You took a pretty good card there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next turn, I'll let you cower before me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.50,0:20:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as I play the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra you've been so eagerly anticipating.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Cower before me"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid {\i1}not{\i0}, Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.57,0:20:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way {\i1}you{\i0} could use Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can call Ra forth is the one who {\i1}masters{\i0} it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.28,0:21:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the person who can read the ancient letters of the Hieratic Text can Summon the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.35,0:21:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.66,0:21:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To put it bluntly, you're no match for me without the aid of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.13,0:21:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.70,0:21:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it. I'll pretend I never saw this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk it up while you {\i1}can{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because {\i1}I'm{\i0} going to win when all is said and done!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright then, let's continue the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.28,0:21:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next turn, we'll Summon the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.34,0:21:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and it'll {\b0}kill{\b1} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.61,0:21:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bakura-{\i1}kun{\i0} finally Summons the Ra card he stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But thanks to a Trap only Malik's dark side knew about,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.57,0:21:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the sacrificed Monster's Attack Points fall to 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.45,0:21:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Ra's Attack Power is 0?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Dark Malik steals the Ra card stolen from him once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:22:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then uses the\N second Special Ability of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.30,0:22:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"One Turn Kill"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.21,0:22:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.08,0:22:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.89,0:22:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.27,0:22:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.82,0:22:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.41,0:22:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.16,0:22:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.14,0:23:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
